Further Developments
This analysis has motivated the hypotheses which we investigate in detail in the upcoming paper “The Split: Analysing Contest Design in the Scottish Premier League.” Using a regression discontinuity (RD) design approach (Thistlethwaite and Campbell 1960) , we will test if The Split dis-incentivised winning and disadvantaged teams in the lower half of the standings. Using data from 2000/01 to 2023/24, we will empirically test whether:

performing with suboptimal effort (“tanking”) occurred for mid-table clubs;
the “split” impacted teams above the cut-off more than those below in terms of (home) attendance;
any home attendance differences may be explained via “superstar” effects.
